descp2: iterable over {str, file-like, int} (Paths of) files to load. If a path ends in ".gz" or ".bz2", it will be uncompressed on the fly. If an integer is passed, it is assumed to be a file descriptor. File-likes and file descriptors will not be closed by this function. File-like objects must be opened in binary mode.
